# Visual & Code Standard Rules

- **CRITICAL**: When adding new Lucide icons, UI components, or utilities, ALWAYS verify that the necessary imports are added to the top of the file to prevent ReferenceErrors at runtime.
- Maintain Thai language support in all UI and file content (UTF-8).
- Prioritize high-end aesthetics (Glassmorphism, gradients, modern typography).
- Verify design consistency across different screen sizes before completion.
- When navigating from a lesson page back to its course detail page, use `navigate(courseDetailPath, { replace: true })` so the browser Back action returns to the course list instead of reopening the lesson.
- The top back button on course detail pages must always navigate statically to `/user/courses`, never use `navigate(-1)` or browser history.
- When the route changes, reset the active scroll container and `window` back to top so each new page starts at the top of the content.
- **Large Desktop Layout**: Maintain a responsive sidebar (`md:260px / xl:280px / 2xl:300px`) and use wider containers (`max-w-[1450px]` - `1600px`) for ultra-wide displays.
- **Container Gutters**: Ensure all main content sections have internal padding (e.g., `xl:px-10 2xl:px-12`) so content never "sticks" to the edges of its max-width container on high-resolution monitors.
- **Document Viewer**: Simplify the desktop UI by hiding the bottom footer bar; integrate the "Mark as Complete" logic into the top close button so closing the viewer automatically saves progress.
- **Mobile Equal Height Cards**: When creating a horizontal scroll container on mobile, ALWAYS use CSS Grid (`grid grid-flow-col auto-cols-[...] items-stretch`) instead of Flexbox to ensure all cards maintain a perfectly equal height regardless of content length. Use a `div` wrapper around interactive elements like `button` inside the grid cells to ensure the browser stretches them correctly.
- **Admin Permissions**: Separate system management (Superadmin) from content management (Sub-admin/Manager). Use `verifySuperAdmin` middleware for sensitive operations (Users, Tiers, Departments, Settings, Rewards) and allow Managers to manage Courses, Lessons, and Reports by using `verifyAdminPanelAccess`.
